paragraph.paragraph:
Although the feature's header comment is optional, most Eiffel programmers and their technical  managers feel that it should never be omitted. Header comments are included by some language processing tools in specialized views of classes. Header comments are almost always short, usually no more than a few lines. Header comments serve to provide a natural language description of what the feature will do (in the case of features that are 


				commands
			) or what information it provides (in the case of 


				queries
			).
